Every year , for many years past , a niece of mine who lives in Flatbush sends me on my birthday a box of plum preserves . 
They have a sentimental value as well . 
I was born in Flatbush , and lived there , during my youth , on my father's estate . 
The city has since grown around the old place , which my niece now owns , but the plum trees stand as they have stood for more than fifty years . 
It was beneath these plum trees . 
Miss Pringle suddenly broke off her face twitched she felt for a handkerchief , and found none she wiped her eyes on her sleeve . 
